  <rte>
    <name>Helvellyn and Fairfield Horseshoe from Patterdale</name>
    <desc>In Summer conditions, this is a very hard Lake District walk, involving over 1,500m of ascent in 21km. In Winter it is a severe route only to be undertaken by people experienced in Winter mountain walking, carrying all the right equipment and preferably in good conditions. Nonetheless, it is a very rewarding Winter day out. </desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1520-description</url>
